BEGIN_PGML
To make fuel for an automobile, you could mix [`x`] gallons of gasoline with [`y`] gallons of ethanol. Suppose that gasoline costs [$Ad] per gallon and ethanol costs [$Bd] per gallon, and you want to mix these types of fuel together to make fuel that costs [$Cd] total. Write a linear equation in standard form that models the amounts of gasoline and ethanol you could mix.

[_]{$evaluator}{16}

END_PGML

